<strong>Junior Womenswear Designer</strong></p>
<p>
At Everlane, we&rsquo;re rethinking the way retail works. We have no physical stores, no middlemen taking their cut and no brand markups. Instead, we design our own luxury basics and sell them exclusively at Everlane.com. Since launching in November 2011, Everlane has attracted over 400,000 members and has been featured in The New York Times, New York Magazine, The Economist, Elle, and GQ.</p>
<p>
&mdash;</p>
<p>
Everlane is building a first-class fashion design team, and we are currently looking for a junior designer that will focus on female apparel and accessories. You must be passionate, enthusiastic, and rigorous, with an obsessive eye for detail. You will join forces with the creative team on initial concept brainstorming, design, and technical design. You will bring your designs to life by reviewing samples, attending fittings, and collaborating with product development, as well as the merchandising and production teams. Our designs are seen by hundreds of thousands of people and are consistently featured in popular fashion publications.</p>
<p>
Our brand ethos and design aesthetic is one of purity and simplicity; less is more. Our vision is to create perfect and timeless wardrobe pieces for every woman (the T-shirt, the silk blouse, the trench, the ballet flat, etc.). All of these are, or will be, part of the Everlane line you will help create. We rely on a maniacal editing process to get these essential pieces just right, from fabric to fit, to drape and construction.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate graduated from a competitive design school and has extensive experience working with highly respected fashion houses. This position is in San Francisco or Los Angeles. Relocation expenses will be covered for candidates outside this area.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Report to the Creative Director in the creation of female apparel and accessories</li>
<li>
Build inspirational concepts and mood boards for product creation</li>
<li>
Hand sketch and create mock up designs on Illustrator for line review</li>
<li>
Work closely with the technical design and product development team to be able to communicate the vision behind the products</li>
<li>
Communicate with factories to express the product details for samples creation</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree from top Fashion Design program</li>
<li>
Several experiences with top fashion brands</li>
<li>
A portfolio that demonstrates your design abilities and style</li>
<li>
Proficient in Illustrator and Photoshop with an understanding of PLM</li>
<li>
A minimalist aesthetic with an eye toward detail and hand feel</li>
<li>
Obsessed with fashion and industrial design</li>
<li>
Positive energy with an ability to take feedback and work in a fast paced environment</li>
<li>
Sewing experience</li>
</ul>
<p>
