<strong>Fabric Developer</strong></p>
<p>
At Everlane, we&rsquo;re rethinking the way retail works. We have no physical stores, no middlemen taking their cut and no brand markups. Instead, we design our own luxury basics and sell them exclusively at Everlane.com. Since launching in November 2011, Everlane has attracted over 400,000 members and has been featured in The New York Times, New York Magazine, The Economist, Elle, and GQ.</p>
<p>
&mdash;</p>
<p>
Everlane is seeking a Fabric Developer to oversee our library and help develop new fabrics. Our belief is that the foundation of all great products starts with the base. In clothing and accessories, that base is the fabric. Our goal is to meet the highest standards of quality (we don&rsquo;t yet). To do this, we want to thoroughly test all of our developments and understand the composition of the fabric, the machinery that was used to create it and the weave.</p>
<p>
You will overtake our current library and establish a program for development and testing. You will work directly with our mills to develop fabric, and then with our testing facility to ensure the fabric meets our standards. The end result will be to create best in class fabrics. The ideal candidate has significant experience in fabric, is highly entrepreneurial and has a deep understanding of fabric theory.</p>
<p>
This position reports directly to the Head of Product and Design and is located in San Francisco.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />
&bull; Oversee current and future fabric developments<br />
&bull; Initiate and follow through testing procedures to establish guidelines that meet Everlane standards<br />
&bull; Create and maintain a fabric library<br />
&bull; Maintain a detailed development calendar and meet necessary dates<br />
&bull; Work directly with mills to develop fabrics for new products and improve fabrics for existing fabrics<br />
&bull; Facilitate seasonal fabric development presentations from mills and vendors to design<br />
&bull; Work with head of design to develop color stories for new season<br />
&bull; Present fabric selections for new products that meet price and quality</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Qualifications:</strong><br />
&bull; 3-5 years working in fabric for a luxury or high-end brand<br />
&bull; Deep knowledge of textiles including: composition, construction and weaving, dyeing and finishing processes (from fiber to finishing)<br />
&bull; Experience working with mills to create best in class fabrics<br />
&bull; Highly inquisitive and able to understand the why behind different testing results or wear tests<br />
&bull; Experience with fabric testing standards and procedures<br />
&bull; Appreciation for beautiful textiles and minimalist design<br />
&bull; Degree in textiles is a plus</p>
